name: Bulbasaur
flavorText: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this Pokémon.

name: Ivysaur
flavorText: There is a plant bulb on its back. When it absorbs nutrients, the bulb is said to blossom into a large flower.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned.

name: Venusaur
flavorText: By spreading the broad petals of its flower and catching the sun's rays, it fills its body with power.
Ability1Text: Each basic Grass Energy attached to your Pokémon provides GrassGrass Energy. You can't apply more than 1 Jungle Totem Ability at a time.

name: Shroomish
flavorText: It prefers damp places. By day it remains still in the forest shade. It releases toxic powder from its head.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Breloom
flavorText: Its short arms stretch when it throws punches. Its technique is equal to that of pro boxers.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep. Your opponent flips 2 coins instead of 1 between turns. If either of them is tails, that Pokémon is still Asleep.

name: Carnivine
flavorText: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon. The new Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Shaymin
flavorText: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.
Attack1Text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw 6 cards.
Attack2Text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack during their last turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Virizion
flavorText: Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.
Attack1Text: You may attach a basic Energy card from your hand to this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Shining Genesect
flavorText: This ancient bug Pokémon was altered by Team Plasma. They upgraded the cannon on its back.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may move a Grass Energy from 1 of your other Pokémon to this Pokémon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage times the amount of Grass Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Entei-GX
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Entei-GX
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Torkoal
flavorText: Coal is the source of Torkoal's energy. Large amounts of coal can be found in the mountains where they live.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's High-Pressure Heat attack does 50 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Larvesta
flavorText: Said to have been born from the sun, it spews fire from its horns and encases itself in a cocoon of fire when it evolves.

name: Volcarona
flavorText: A sea of fire engulfs the surroundings of their battles, since they use their six wings to scatter their ember scales.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may have your opponent switch their Active Pokémon with 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

name: Reshiram
flavorText: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with fire. It helps those who want to build a world of truth.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon can't attack during your next turn.

name: Litten
flavorText: While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.

name: Torracat
flavorText: At its throat, it bears a bell of fire. The bell rings brightly whenever this Pokémon spits fire.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Incineroar
flavorText: This Pokémon has a violent, selfish disposition. If it's not in the mood to listen, it will ignore its Trainer's orders with complete nonchalance.
Attack1Text: If your Benched Pokémon have any damage counters on them, this attack does 80 more damage.
Attack2Text: Discard all Fire Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Totodile
flavorText: It is small but rough and tough. It won't hesitate to take a bite out of anything that moves.

name: Croconaw
flavorText: If it loses a fang, a new one grows back in its place. There are always 48 fangs lining its mouth.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is on your Bench, you may move all Energy from your Active Pokémon to this Pokémon. If you do, switch it with your Active Pokémon.

name: Feraligatr
flavorText: It usually moves slowly, but it goes at blinding speed when it attacks and bites prey.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Qwilfish
flavorText: To fire its poison spikes, it must inflate its body by drinking over 2.6 gallons of water all at once.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Buizel
flavorText: It swims by rotating its two tails like a screw. When it dives, its flotation sac collapses.

name: Floatzel
flavorText: It floats using its well-developed flotation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon does 30 damage to itself.

name: Palkia
flavorText: It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimension parallel to ours. It appears in mythology.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Manaphy
flavorText: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokémon.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may heal 20 damage from 1 of your Pokémon that has any Water Energy attached to it.

name: Keldeo
flavorText: It crosses the world, running over the surfaces of oceans and rivers. It appears at scenic waterfronts.
Attack1Text: Put a Water Pokémon from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

name: Shining Volcanion
flavorText: It lets out billows of steam and disappears into the dense fog. It's said to live in mountains where humans do not tread.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Raichu-GX
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage times the amount of Lightning Energy attached to your Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon does 30 damage to itself.

name: Voltorb
flavorText: It was discovered when Poké Balls were introduced. It is said that there is some connection.

name: Electrode
flavorText: It explodes in response to even minor stimuli. It is feared, with the nickname of "The Bomb Ball."
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, or any other effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Raikou
flavorText: The rain clouds it carries let it fire thunderbolts at will. They say that it descended with lightning.
Attack1Text: Attach a Lightning Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Plusle
flavorText: It cheers on friends with pom-poms made of sparks. It drains power from telephone poles.
Attack1Text: If Minun is on your Bench, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Minun
flavorText: Exposure to electricity from Minun and Plusle promotes blood circulation and relaxes muscles.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Zekrom
flavorText: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with lightning. It assists those who want to build an ideal world.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Ekans
flavorText: The older it gets, the longer it grows. At night, it wraps its long body around tree branches to rest.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Arbok
flavorText: The pattern on its belly appears to be a frightening face. Weak foes will flee just at the sight of the pattern.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks do 30 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Jynx
flavorText: It wiggles its hips as it walks. It can cause people to dance in unison with it.
Attack1Text: Choose a random card from your opponent's hand. Your opponent reveals that card and shuffles it into their deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Mewtwo-GX
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage times the amount of Energy attached to this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Shining Mew
flavorText: Because it can use all kinds of moves, many scientists believe Mew to be the ancestor of Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Latios
flavorText: A highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its wings in flight, it can overtake jet planes.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Shining Jirachi
flavorText: Generations have believed that any wish written on a note on its head will come true when it awakens.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is an evolved Pokémon, devolve it by putting all of the Evolution cards on it into your opponent's hand.

name: Golett
flavorText: The energy that burns inside it enables it to move, but no one has yet been able to identify this energy.

name: Golurk
flavorText: It is said that Golurk were ordered to protect people and Pokémon by the ancient people who made them.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 60 more damage for each heads.

name: Marshadow
flavorText: Able to conceal itself in shadows, it never appears before humans, so its very existence was the stuff of myth.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may have each player shuffle their hand into their deck and draw 4 cards.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Stunfisk
flavorText: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Spiritomb
flavorText: A Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits. It is bound to a fissure in an odd keystone.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, your opponent's Active Pokémon can't retreat.
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like.

name: Purrloin
flavorText: Its cute act is a ruse. When victims let down their guard, they find their items taken. It attacks with sharp claws.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Liepard
flavorText: Their beautiful form comes from the muscles they have developed. They run silently in the night.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks. That Pokémon can't use that attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Scraggy
flavorText: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Scrafty
flavorText: It pulls up its shed skin to protect itself while it kicks. The bigger the crest, the more respected it is.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Basic Pokémon, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Zorua
flavorText: It changes so it looks like its foe, tricks it, and then uses that opportunity to flee.

name: Zoroark-GX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a card from your hand. If you do, draw 2 cards.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Pokémon in play.
Attack2Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Yveltal
flavorText: When this legendary Pokémon's wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Attach a Darkness Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Hoopa
flavorText: In its true form, it possess a huge amount of power. Legends of its avarice tell how it once carried off an entire castle to gain the treasure hidden within.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon by your opponent's Pokémon-GX or Pokémon-EX.

name: Shining Rayquaza
flavorText: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.
Attack1Text: Discard the top 2 cards of your deck.
Attack2Text: Discard 3 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Shining Arceus
flavorText: According to the legends of Sinnoh, this Pokémon emerged from an egg and shaped all there is in this world.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, prevent all damage done to your Benched Pokémon by your opponent's attacks.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Entei-GX
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage times the amount of Energy attached to this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage times the amount of Lightning Energy attached to your Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon does 30 damage to itself.

Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage times the amount of Energy attached to this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a card from your hand. If you do, draw 2 cards.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Pokémon in play.
Attack2Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Zoroark-GX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a card from your hand. If you do, draw 2 cards.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Pokémon in play.
Attack2Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)
